text: Romaine Quinn (born July 30, 1990) is an American politician. From Rice Lake, Wisconsin, Quinn graduated from Rice Lake High School and received his bachelor's degree from University of Wisconsin–Green Bay in political science and public leadership. Quinn worked for Viking Coca-Cola. Quinn is a Republican.Republican Assembly Campaign Committee-Romaine Quinn Quinn served as Mayor of Rice Lake, Wisconsin,Romaine Quinn For 75th Assembly District becoming the youngest mayor to serve in Rice Lake history. On November 4, 2014, Quinn defeated the incumbent Stephen Smith for the Wisconsin State Assembly seat.Election results In March 2020, Quinn announced he would not run for re-election to the Wisconsin State Assembly. ==References== Category:Living people Category:People from Rice Lake, Wisconsin Category:University of Wisconsin–Green Bay alumni Category:Businesspeople from Wisconsin Category:Wisconsin Republicans Category:Mayors of places in Wisconsin Category:Members of the Wisconsin State Assembly Category:1990 births Category:21st-century American politicians
